      "block_id": "p16_b1",
      "translation": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b2",
      "translation": "Group Chief Executive Officer and President's Report"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b3",
      "translation": "We recognize there is still much work ahead in this important area. We have also recently completed a review of our Environmental, Social and Governance strategy. I am confident that our"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b4",
      "translation": "five strategic focus areas: enhancing physical and mental wellbeing, green operations, sustainable investment, talent and culture, and effective governance, will help us achieve our aspiration to lead the global industry in"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b5",
      "translation": "environmental, social and governance matters."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b6",
      "translation": "Outlook"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b7",
      "translation": "In 2020, the COVID-19 pandemic was undoubtedly the largest-scale public health emergency in our living memory. Affected businesses and households"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b8",
      "translation": "received unprecedented public financial and monetary support, which helped mitigate some of the extreme financial shocks caused by the pandemic and accelerated the pace of recovery, which was particularly evident in"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b9",
      "translation": "countries with sound health policies and infrastructure. However, there are significant differences between countries. In this challenging environment, Asia (excluding Japan) recorded"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b10",
      "translation": "the relatively strongest global GDP performance. Currently, the global economy is just beginning to emerge from a deep recession and entering the early stages of improvement."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b11",
      "translation": ""
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b12",
      "translation": "Although the impact of the pandemic is not yet over, we believe 2021 will be a transitional year and we remain cautiously optimistic. The market anticipates the rollout of"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b13",
      "translation": "vaccination programs and new therapies to help reduce infection rates and severity of the disease, enabling healthcare systems to respond more effectively and reduce mortality. Although we"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b14",
      "translation": "do not expect outdoor activities and consumer behavior to return to pre-pandemic levels in the short term, as consumer confidence recovers, the scope of recovery is expected to gradually"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b15",
      "translation": "expand from manufacturing-led industries to consumer and service sectors. This will be particularly evident in countries with younger populations."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b16",
      "translation": "I am confident about AIA's long-term prospects. Despite near-term uncertainties, strong domestic drivers of demand, combined with Asia's key"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b17",
      "translation": "demographic trends, continue to provide positive structural support for AIA's long-term outlook. With rising incomes, low private insurance penetration, and"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b18",
      "translation": "limited social welfare coverage, demand for AIA's products will continue to grow. We will leverage our substantial competitive advantages and strong"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b19",
      "translation": "track record of growth to build a more sustainable future for our communities and create shared value for all stakeholders."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b20",
      "translation": "Lee Yuan Siong"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b21",
      "translation": "Group Chief Executive Officer and President"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b22",
      "translation": "12 March 2021"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b23",
      "translation": "Growth rates are presented at constant exchange rates, which management believes provides a clearer picture of year-on-year business performance."
    },
    {
